Package edu.wmich.cs1120.la5

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    IArea
    This interface provides the contract by which other classes may use to define an area
    IExpression
    This interface provides basic structure of further Expressions.
    IMapCreator
    This interface provides the framework of how a class should parse data from a file and send data to the TerrainScanner
    IOperation
    This interface holds the method to be further defined to act upon two Expressions
    IRover
    This interface provides the methods used for evaluating the path to be taken per the information requested.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    Addition
    This class adds two values determined by type expressed by the expressions passed.
    Area
    This class provides the base implementation further utilized by HighArea and LowArea to describe an region the rover would enter.
    BinaryExpression
    Class represents a simple binary read from a .dat file.
    ElevationAnalyzer
    This class represents the part of the rover that can evaluate the elevation of a cell/Area visited.
    EnergyAnalyzer
    This class represents the part of the rover that can evaluate the energy needed to traverse a cell/Area.
    ExpressionFactory
    This class provides a method to evaluate an expression and determines the action upon said expression.
    HighArea
    This class provides the means of defining and acting upon an Area.
    LA5Main
    This is the main entry point of the program.
    Literal
    This class LITERALLY expresses a value held by an Expression
    LowArea
    This Class functions as a concrete object of type Area It's defining characteristic is to provide a means of calculating energy consumed.
    MapCreatorFromDat
    This class takes a binary file and interprets the data within and sends it to the TerrainScanner.
    MapCreatorFromTxt
    This class takes a text file and interprets the data within and sends it to the TerrainScanner.
    RadiationAnalyzer
    This class represents the part of the rover that can evaluate the radiation of a cell/Area visited.
    Subtraction
    This class subtracts two values determined by type expressed by the expressions passed.
